ISSUED AT 0600 WEDNESDAY 04 DECEMBER 2013
1. GALE WARNING: IN OPERATION SMALL CRAFT WARNING: SEE GALE WARNING
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0300: A COLD FRONT IS CLEARING THE SOUTH
OF IRELAND IN A MODERATE TO FRESH WEST TO NORTHWEST WIND. A DEVELOPING LOW
TO THE SOUTH OF ICELAND WILL MOVE TO THE NORTH OF IRELAND LATER TONIGHT
STEERING IN GALE TO STORM FORCE WESTERLY WINDS.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD AND
THE NORTH IRISH SEA:
WIND: NORTHWEST FORCE 5 OR 6 AND GUSTY BACKING WEST TO SOUTHWEST THIS
EVENING AND INCREASING FORCE 6 TO GALE FORCE 8 AND GUSTY. FURTHER INCREASING
STRONG GALE FORCE OVERNIGHT AND TOUCHING STORM FORCE 10 FOR NORTH AND NORTHEAST
SEA AREAS LATER IN THE NORTH IRISH SEA TOO.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM HOWTH HEAD TO ROCHE'S PT TO SLYNE HEAD AND THE
SOUTH IRISH SEA:
WIND NORTHWESTERLY FORCE 4 TO 6. BACKING WESTERLY THIS AFTERNOON AND INCREASING
FORCE 5 OR 6 AND GUSTY LATER THIS EVENING OR EARLY TONIGHT. FURTHER INCREASING
GALE FORCE 8 LATER TONIGHT.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEAS AREAS: PATCHY RAIN IN THE SOUTH. BECOMING MAINLY FAIR
OR FINE. JUST SOME PASSING SHOWERS IN THE NORTH AND WEST (RISK OF HAIL).
RAIN ARRIVING INTO NORTHERN AREAS BY THIS TIME TOMORROW.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: MODERATE OR POOR IN ANY RAIN OR DRIZZLE
OTHERWISE GOOD.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: NIL
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 FRIDAY 05 DECEMBER 2013: GALE
TO STORM FORCE WEST TO NORTHWEST WINDS VERY GRADUALLY MODERATING ON THURSDAY.
HEAVY RAIN MOVING SOUTHWARDS THURSDAY DAY BUT BECOMING MORE SCATTERED AS
IT DOES SO. MAINLY FAIR OR FINE WEATHER FOLLOWING - WELL SCATTERED SHOWERS
(THREAT OF HAIL).
WARNING OF HEAVY ATLANTIC SWELL: NIL
